FL,359,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F358A1782402488
OL,3,CSchools shut early due to extreme heat
OL,4,Cas temperatures may hit 40 degrees
OL,6,FMonday's weather forecast across
OL,7,FJersey and Guernsey:
OL,9,FThis is the second spell of very hot
OL,10,Fweather in recent weeks, following the
OL,11,Fend of May heatwave, where
OL,12,Ftemperatures reached a record 34
OL,13,Fdegrees for that month.
OL,15,FIt saw disruption at Jersey's General
OL,16,FHospital as more than 80 patients had
OL,17,Ftheir surgeries postponed due to an
OL,18,Fair-con failure - the issue has since
OL,19,Fbeen fixed.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/10
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,359,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F358A1782402488
OL,3,CSchools shut early due to extreme heat
OL,4,Cas temperatures may hit 40 degrees
OL,6,FGuernsey's Princess Elizabeth Hospital
OL,7,Falso declared a critical incident
OL,8,Fduring that time as it faced a high
OL,9,Fdemand for beds, although officials
OL,10,Fsaid it was not linked to the hot
OL,11,Fweather.
OL,13,FWhy humidity matters:
OL,15,FThis week will see similar
OL,16,Ftemperatures in Jersey to its hottest
OL,17,Fday on record - 37.9 degrees Celsius
OL,18,Fon 18 July 2022.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/10
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,359,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F358A1782402488
OL,3,CSchools shut early due to extreme heat
OL,4,Cas temperatures may hit 40 degrees
OL,6,FHowever, the air is much more humid
OL,7,Fthis time around, which makes it that
OL,8,Fmuch harder to cool down.
OL,10,FOn a hot but dry day, you would sweat
OL,11,Fand that would evaporate off your body
OL,12,Fto help regulate your temperature.
OL,14,FHowever, because it is much more
OL,15,Fhumid, when you sweat, the air is
OL,16,Falready saturated with moisture and
OL,17,Fthere is nowhere for it to go.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/10
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,359,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F358A1782402488
OL,3,CSchools shut early due to extreme heat
OL,4,Cas temperatures may hit 40 degrees
OL,6,FInstead of evaporating, it stays on
OL,7,Fyour body, meaning you do not get the
OL,8,Fbenefit of the cooling effect and you
OL,9,Ffeel clammy.
OL,11,FThere's a meteorological measurement
OL,12,Fto track humidity called the dew point.
OL,14,FIn July 2022 for the previous record-
OL,15,Fbreaking temperature, this was in
OL,16,Fsingle figures, according to the UK
OL,17,FMet Office. This week, it will be
OL,18,Fsignificantly higher, with predictions
OL,19,Fin the teens or maybe even hitting 20.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/10
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,359,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F358A1782402488
OL,3,CSchools shut early due to extreme heat
OL,4,Cas temperatures may hit 40 degrees
OL,6,FSo, similar temperatures but it is
OL,7,Fgoing to feel worse - a mugginess
OL,8,Fwhich would be more at home in
OL,9,FSingapore or Thailand.
OL,11,FWhy is Jersey often hotter than
OL,12,FGuernsey?
OL,14,FIt is a question that comes up when
OL,15,Fthe islands face periods of hot
OL,16,Fweather - why do temperatures seem
OL,17,Fconsistently higher in Jersey than
OL,18,FGuernsey?
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G9/10
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,359,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F358A1782402488
OL,3,CSchools shut early due to extreme heat
OL,4,Cas temperatures may hit 40 degrees
OL,6,FWell Guernsey receives a greater
OL,7,Fcooling effect from the open sea,
OL,8,Fwhile Jersey is closer to France.
OL,10,FLand also retains a huge amount of
OL,11,Fheat so, if two islands are close
OL,12,Ftogether, the smaller one is likely to
OL,13,Fbe cooler.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G10/10
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
